{\\pard\\li0\\sa120\\cf1\\f0\\fs22 That looks like {\\b creeping buttercup} ({\\i Ranunculus repens}) \\u8212? note the three-lobed leaves with pale patches and the runners spreading along the ground. It's common in damp lawns. If you want it gone, dig out the runners before it flowers; mowing alone won't stop it.\\par}
}"
`;

